# Financial Risk Capital Adequacy Perpetual Cumulative Subordinated Debt Amount

## identifier
de7721

## type
float

## definition
This is the value, as at the relevant date, of paid up perpetual cumulative subordinated debt on issue by the reporting party.

This item is calculated for capital adequacy purposes and is to be determined in accordance with relevant prudential standards.

## syntax
### xbrl
- balance=credit
- name=FinancialRisk.CapitalAdequacy.PerpetualCumulativeSubordinatedDebt.Amount
- classification=baf/bafot/bafot.02.06
- period=instant
